caller_intent: Timothy Smith (and Blake Smith) is seeking a health insurance quote for their small business, Smith Auto and Truck Service, which employs four people. They want to explore options for 50% payment terms and are looking for an alternative to their current United Healthcare provider through a broker.
resolution_steps: Agent Heather confirms the call is about business health insurance and notes the company has no existing insurance.
Heather checks availability of Steve Edmund, the health insurance specialist, and sends him a chat message.
Heather collects contact details (Blake Smith, phone number, company name, and location details).
Informs caller that Steve is unavailable but will respond by Monday.
knowledge_required: Understanding small business health insurance options
Ability to route calls to specialized agents (Steve Edmund)
systems_referenced: Internal chat system for agent communication
summary: A business owner seeks health insurance quotes for their four-employee auto service company. The agent connects them with the health insurance specialist, collects necessary details, and schedules a follow-up when the specialist becomes available. The caller is dissatisfied with their current provider and prefers direct broker assistance.
